[00:31.23]he said that business was very bad.|他说生意非常糟糕。
[00:35.10]He told me that the firm could not afford to pay such large salaries.|他告诉我，公司无力支付如此高的薪水。
[00:41.52]Twenty people had already left.|已经有二十个人离开了。
[00:45.06]I knew that my turn had come.|我知道我的时刻终于到了。
[00:48.59]'Mr. Harmsworth,' I said in a weak voice.|“哈姆斯沃思先生，”我虚弱地说道。
